{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"ScreenDetailed: left property","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/left","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.ScreenDetailed.left"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window_Management_API\">Window Management API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed\"><code>ScreenDetailed</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/availLeft\"><code>availLeft</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/availTop\"><code>availTop</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/devicePixelRatio\"><code>devicePixelRatio</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/isInternal\"><code>isInternal</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/isPrimary\"><code>isPrimary</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/label\"><code>label</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><em><code>left</code> <abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/top\"><code>top</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Screen\"><code>Screen</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Window Management API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/requestFullscreen\"><code>Element.requestFullscreen()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Screen/isExtended\"><code>Screen.isExtended</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetails\"><code>ScreenDetails</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/getScreenDetails\"><code>Window.getScreenDetails()</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<p>\n  The <strong><code>left</code></strong> read-only property of the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed\"><code>ScreenDetailed</code></a> interface is a number representing the x-coordinate (left-hand edge) of the total screen area inside the OS virtual screen arrangement, relative to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window_Management_API/Multi-screen_origin\">multi-screen origin</a>.\n</p>\n<p>This is equal to the true left-hand edge, ignoring any OS UI element drawn at the left of the screen. Windows cannot be placed in those areas; to get the left-hand coordinate of the screen area that windows can be placed in, use <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ScreenDetailed/availLeft\"><code>ScreenDetailed.availLeft</code></a>.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> In Firefox, a non-standard implementation of the <code>left</code> property is available on the <code>Screen</code> interface. See the <a href=\"#non-standard_example\">Non-standard example</a> below for usage details, and see the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Screen#browser_compatibility\"><code>Screen</code></a> reference page for browser support information relating to the non-standard implementation.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>A number.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"window_management_api_example","title":"Window Management API example","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// Available in browsers that support the Window Management API</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> screenDetails <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> window<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getScreenDetails</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Return the absolute left value of the first screen</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> screen1Left <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> screenDetails<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>screens<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>left<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"non-standard_example","title":"Non-standard example","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// Available in Firefox</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Return the absolute left value of the current screen</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> screenLeft <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> window<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>screen<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>left<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/window-management/#ref-for-dom-screendetailed-left","title":"Window Management"}],"query":"api.ScreenDetailed.left"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.ScreenDetailed.left"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window_Management_API\">Window Management API</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The left read-only property of the\n  ScreenDetailed 